            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>Carry over your save data to the full game when it launches.</span>
      </p></div><div><p>A demo for the <a title="Platforms > Switch 2 [1,049 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a> and <a title="Platforms > Switch [18,382 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a> versions of <em><a title="Games > Digimon Story: Time Stranger [27 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/digimon-story-time-stranger">Digimon Story: Time Stranger</a></em> is now available via <a title="Platforms > Nintendo [23,696 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo">Nintendo</a> eShop, publisher <a title="Companies > Bandai Namco Entertainment [6,839 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/bandai-namco-entertainment">Bandai Namco</a> and developer <a title="Companies > Media.Vision [245 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/media-vision">Media.Vision</a>. <span id="more-1058547"></span></p><p>Like the existing demo on PlayStation 5, Xbox Series, and PC, save data from the Switch 2 and Switch demo can be carried over to the full game when it launches.</p><p><em>Digimon Story: Time Stranger</em> is available now for PlayStation 5, Xbox Series, and PC via <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1984270/Digimon_Story_Time_Stranger/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steam</a>, and is coming to Switch 2 and Switch on July 9 in Japan and July 10 worldwide.</p><p>Watch a new trailer below.</p><h2><span>How-To Play / Demo Trailer</span></h2><p><strong>English</strong></p><!-- AD: content -->
